    <member name="N:Remotion.Web.UI">
      <summary>
    The <b>Remotion.Web.UI</b> namespace provides classes related the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Page" /> and 
    generic user interface features.
  
    <h3 class="dtH3"><a name="wai">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 1.0 (WCAG 1.0)</a></h3><!-- HTML Help requires separate anchor tag for target -->     
    <para>
      The <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/intro/wcag.php" target="_blank">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 1.0</a> 
      defined by the <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI" target="_blank">Web Accessibility Initiative (WAI)</a> include a 
      <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG10/full-checklist.html" target="_blank">list of checkpoints</a> which must be 
      met by a web page claiming WCAG 1.0 conformance. These checkpoints have one of three priority levels assigned. 
    </para><para>
      The WCAG conformance of a web page is meassured by its conformence level:
    </para>
    <div class="tablediv"> 
    <table class="dtTABLE" cellspacing="0">
      <colgroup>
        <col width="25%" />
        <col width="75%" />
      </colgroup>
      <thead>
        <tr valign="top">
          <th>Conformance Level</th>
          <th>Requirement</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Conformance Level "A"</td>
          <td>All Priority 1 checkpoints are satisfied.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Conformance Level "Double-A"</td>
          <td>All Priority 1 and 2 checkpoints are satisfied.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Conformance Level "Triple-A"</td>
          <td>All Priority 1, 2, and 3 checkpoints are satisfied.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    </div>
    <para>
      A web application implemented with the use of the Remotion web controls can enforce WCAG 1.0 level A conformance.
      This feature is activated by setting the <c>wcag</c> entry in the configuration file. This entry maps to an 
      instance of the <see cref="T:Remotion.Web.Configuration.WcagConfiguration" /> type. (See the documentation of 
      <see cref="T:Remotion.Web.Configuration.WebConfiguration">Remotion.Web.Configuration.WebConfiguration</see> for 
      details on using the configuration file.)
    </para><para>
      It remains the developer's responsibility to ensure conformance with 
      all checkpoints related to inter-control relationships and the web application's content itself.
    </para><para>
      A list of WCAG conform controls can be found in the 
      <see cref="N:Remotion.Web.UI.Controls"/> and <see cref="N:Remotion.ObjectBinding.Web.UI.Controls"/> namespace documentation.
    </para>
  </summary>
    </member>
